Kim Winona https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Winona 0 Kim Winona (October 10, 1930 – June 23, 1978) was a Native American actress. A Sioux Native American, Winona appeared with Keith Larsen in the CBS western television series Brave Eagle during 1955-1956 season.Born in Nebraska as Constance Elaine Mackey, Winona grew up first on the Rosebud Reservation n South Dakota and later in Spokane, Washington.She was 25 years old when she landed the role of Morning Star, the romantic interest of Larsen's title role of Brave Eagle on Brave Eagle. A Roy Rogers production, Brave Eagle was the first series to present events from the view of the Native Indian protagonists.
